      <ProgramInformation programId='crid://bbc.co.uk/3257009522'>
        <BasicDescription>
          <Title><![CDATA[A Whole Lotta Shakin']]></Title>
          <Synopsis length='short'><![CDATA[The 50th Anniversary Of Sun Records: A four-part documentary marking the historic 50th anniversary of the founding of Sun Records, the record label of such legends as Elvis Presley and Roy Orbison.]]></Synopsis>
          <Synopsis length='long'><![CDATA[The 50th Anniversary Of Sun Records

A four part series presented by Steve Harley celebrating the 50th Anniversary of Sun Records of Memphis, the record company that at one time had Elvis Presley, Jerry Lee Lewis, Carl Perkins, Johnny Cash, Roy Orbison and Charlie Rich on its books. 

The phenomenal success of Sun Records was due to the vision of local Memphis entrepreneur Sam Phillips. Before the white rock 'n' rollers put Sun into the pop charts, Phillips started out recording local black blues artistes, but when a young truck driver called Elvis Presley walked through the front door of Sun Records planning to record a song as a present for his mother, the course of modern musical history was changed dramatically.]]></Synopsis>
